<li><a href="http://www.quora.com/Medicine-and-Healthcare/Why-does-the-USA-spend-a-lot-more-per-person-on-medical-care-than-other-first-world-countries-and-yet-gets-worse-results-on-average/answer/Dan-Munro" class="rsswidget" title='&lt;div style="color: #666666"&gt;In Medicine and Healthcare: Mike Kurz voted up this answer.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;div id="ld_wbbksy_3574"&gt;&lt;div style="font-weight: bold; color: #000000"&gt;&lt;div class="hover_menu hidden hover_menu_wide hover_menu_cards" style="display: none" id="__w2_JgXvrFR_menu"&gt;&lt;div class="hover_menu_nub"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class="hover_menu_contents" id="__w2_JgXvrFR_menu_contents"&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;a class="user" href="/Dan-Munro" action_mousedown="UserLinkClickthrough" id="__w2_JgXvrFR_link"&gt;Dan Munro&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Not to be flippant, but the answer is relatively short (and I&amp;#039;ve worked around healthcare for about 15 years - mostly from the vantage point of early stage software/technology ventures).&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;i&gt;The U.S. system has been optimized around revenue and profits - not safety and quality. &lt;/i&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;This has resulted in some VERY sobering headlines:&lt;br /&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span class="qlink_container"&gt;&lt;a href="http://www.propublica.org/article/how-many-die-from-medical-mistakes-in-us-hospitals" class="external_link" target="_blank" onmouseover="return require(&amp;quot;qtext&amp;quot;).tooltip(this, &amp;quot;propublica.org&amp;quot;)"&gt;How Many Die From Medical Mistakes in U.S. Hospitals? (ProPublica)&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt; [hint - it&amp;#039;s now the 3rd leading cause of &lt;span class="qlink_container"&gt;&lt;a href="/Death-and-Dying-1"&gt;death&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt; in the U.S. behind heart disease and cancer]&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;To put that figure (a range of 210,000 to 440,000 per year) in some perspective - it&amp;#039;s effectively the equivalent of the world&amp;#039;s largest passenger airliner - the Airbus A-380 - crashing daily - with no survivors. Reaction would be swift and global - and likely have every version of the A-380 grounded by day 3. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;img class="landscape qtext_image zoomable_in zoomable_in_feed" src="http://qph.is.quoracdn.net/main-qimg-457bf7f19a1fbaf2731f7e0a26e74867?convert_to_webp=true" master_src="http://qph.is.quoracdn.net/main-qimg-df15213f634ce6ba16ecf925ba9e3892?convert_to_webp=true" master_w="991" master_h="576"/&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;The U.S. healthcare industry is basically an economic unit the size of Germany&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span class="qlink_container"&gt;&lt;a href="http://www.forbes.com/sites/danmunro/2014/06/16/u-s-healthcare-ranked-dead-last-compared-to-10-other-countries/" class="external_link" target="_blank" onmouseover="return require(&amp;quot;qtext&amp;quot;).tooltip(this, &amp;quot;forbes.com&amp;quot;)"&gt;U.S. Healthcare Ranked Dead Last Compared To 10 Other Countries (Forbes - mine)&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;br /&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span class="qlink_container"&gt;&lt;a href="http://www.commonwealthfund.org/publications/press-releases/2013/apr/new-health-insurance-survey" rel="nofollow" class="external_link" target="_blank" onmouseover="return require(&amp;quot;qtext&amp;quot;).tooltip(this, &amp;quot;commonwealthfund.org&amp;quot;)"&gt;New Health Insurance Survey: 84 Million People Were Uninsured for a Time or Underinsured in 2012 (The Commonwealth Fund)&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;br /&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;There&amp;#039;s also a two sentence quote (not mine) that highlights why it&amp;#039;s so hard to change the U.S. healthcare system:&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;img class="landscape qtext_image zoomable_in zoomable_in_feed" src="http://qph.is.quoracdn.net/main-qimg-5ca51e9128753b0c05c87f5714d57da1?convert_to_webp=true" master_src="http://qph.is.quoracdn.net/main-qimg-d4ea5b38bf0bc34917e0a3a3050ce799?convert_to_webp=true" master_w="945" master_h="571"/&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;a style="font-weight: bold" href="http://www.quora.com/Medicine-and-Healthcare/Why-does-the-USA-spend-a-lot-more-per-person-on-medical-care-than-other-first-world-countries-and-yet-gets-worse-results-on-average"&gt;See question on Quora&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/div&gt;'>Why does the USA spend a lot more per person on medical care than other first world countries and yet gets worse results on average?</a></li>
<li><a href="http://www.quora.com/Video-Games/Is-BioShock-Infinite-really-that-good" class="rsswidget" title='&lt;div style="color: #666666"&gt;In Video Games: Mike Kurz followed a question.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;div id="ld_wbbksy_3575"&gt;&lt;span id="ld_wbbksy_3576"&gt;6 Answers&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;a style="font-weight: bold" href="http://www.quora.com/Video-Games/Is-BioShock-Infinite-really-that-good"&gt;See question on Quora&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;br /&gt;'>Is BioShock Infinite really that good?</a></li>
<li><a href="http://www.quora.com/Video-Games/Is-BioShock-Infinite-really-that-good/answer/Mike-Kurz" class="rsswidget" title='&lt;div style="color: #666666"&gt;In Video Games: Mike Kurz added this answer.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;div id="ld_wbbksy_3577"&gt;&lt;div style="font-weight: bold; color: #000000"&gt;&lt;div class="hover_menu hidden hover_menu_wide hover_menu_cards" style="display: none" id="__w2_BkgzqFJ_menu"&gt;&lt;div class="hover_menu_nub"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class="hover_menu_contents" id="__w2_BkgzqFJ_menu_contents"&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;a class="user" href="/Mike-Kurz" action_mousedown="UserLinkClickthrough" id="__w2_BkgzqFJ_link"&gt;Mike Kurz&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;br /&gt;From the perspective of a critic, yes, Bioshock Infinite is really that good. It tells a great story, and really makes you examine your actions as the player. The payoff at the end is crazy good. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;That being said, &amp;quot;good&amp;quot; is subjective. If you really despise first person shooters and sci fi stories you&amp;#039;re not going to like it. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Personally this is one of the few games I point non-gamers at as a good representative of what the medium can do when it comes to storytelling and engaging the player. Infinite has a great plot, a very well realized world, and good characters. It&amp;#039;s just a great game.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;a style="font-weight: bold" href="http://www.quora.com/Video-Games/Is-BioShock-Infinite-really-that-good"&gt;See question on Quora&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/div&gt;'>Is BioShock Infinite really that good?</a></li>
<li><a href="http://www.quora.com/Xbox-360/Which-Xbox-360-game-has-the-best-story-in-your-opinion" class="rsswidget" title='&lt;div style="color: #666666"&gt;In Xbox 360: Mike Kurz followed a question.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;div id="ld_wbbksy_3578"&gt;&lt;span id="ld_wbbksy_3579"&gt;5 Answers&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;a style="font-weight: bold" href="http://www.quora.com/Xbox-360/Which-Xbox-360-game-has-the-best-story-in-your-opinion"&gt;See question on Quora&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;br /&gt;'>Which Xbox 360 game has the best story in your opinion?</a></li>
<li><a href="http://www.quora.com/Xbox-360/Which-Xbox-360-game-has-the-best-story-in-your-opinion/answer/Mike-Kurz" class="rsswidget" title='&lt;div style="color: #666666"&gt;In Xbox 360: Mike Kurz added this answer.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;div id="ld_wbbksy_3580"&gt;&lt;div style="font-weight: bold; color: #000000"&gt;&lt;div class="hover_menu hidden hover_menu_wide hover_menu_cards" style="display: none" id="__w2_Kx3WFAZ_menu"&gt;&lt;div class="hover_menu_nub"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class="hover_menu_contents" id="__w2_Kx3WFAZ_menu_contents"&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;a class="user" href="/Mike-Kurz" action_mousedown="UserLinkClickthrough" id="__w2_Kx3WFAZ_link"&gt;Mike Kurz&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;br /&gt;There are a lot of great choices here, and I can&amp;#039;t narrow it down to just one, so here&amp;#039;s my top three: &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Bioshock Infinite&lt;br /&gt;The Walking Dead (the one by Telltale, not the new shooter)&lt;br /&gt;The Mass Effect Trilogy.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;a style="font-weight: bold" href="http://www.quora.com/Xbox-360/Which-Xbox-360-game-has-the-best-story-in-your-opinion"&gt;See question on Quora&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/div&gt;'>Which Xbox 360 game has the best story in your opinion?</a></li>
