<li><a href="http://www.quora.com/Video-Games/Why-cant-we-have-an-Indian-themed-Assassins-Creed/answer/Mike-Kurz" class="rsswidget" title='&lt;div style="color: #666666"&gt;In Video Games: Mike Kurz added this answer.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;div id="ld_wbbksy_3583"&gt;&lt;div style="font-weight: bold; color: #000000"&gt;&lt;div class="hover_menu hidden hover_menu_wide hover_menu_cards" style="display: none" id="__w2_sTlMDHy_menu"&gt;&lt;div class="hover_menu_nub"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class="hover_menu_contents" id="__w2_sTlMDHy_menu_contents"&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;a class="user" href="/Mike-Kurz" action_mousedown="UserLinkClickthrough" id="__w2_sTlMDHy_link"&gt;Mike Kurz&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Canonically speaking, there&amp;#039;s no reason Ubisoft couldn&amp;#039;t do an Indian themed AC game. In fact, I&amp;#039;m with you - it&amp;#039;d probably be an interesting setting for an AC game. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Ubisoft picks their settings for AC games in a very methodical way. They look at what sort of settings are going to fit well with current &lt;span class="qlink_container"&gt;&lt;a href="/News-Entertainment-and-Pop-Culture"&gt;pop culture&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt; trends, and they also do a lot of surveys and polls to see what settings people are interested in. If you&amp;#039;d like to see an AC set in India, keep talking about it - if other people agree, and Ubisoft sees the public interest in an Indian AC I&amp;#039;d imagine they would at least give it some thought.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;a style="font-weight: bold" href="http://www.quora.com/Video-Games/Why-cant-we-have-an-Indian-themed-Assassins-Creed"&gt;See question on Quora&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/div&gt;'>Why can't we have an Indian themed Assassin's Creed?</a></li>
